    <note>Zhou(1) Ling [496] He is identified as a Danyang Zhou in the funerary inscription for his son-in-law, Hua(2) Zhiwen [18910] (q.v.), which is a positive identification since his titular office in the funerary inscription is the same as the one he holds in Ouyang Xiu's edict of appointment as Jinghu Nan yunshi. XCB, 146.6b, 152.5b, 153.11a, 157.16a, 157.16a (n.); Guangxi TZ, 21.15b; Ouyang Xiu, WJ, 79.11a, 81.9b; SHY:ZG, 42.16b. CBD, 2, 1448.</note>
